{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Stuffing","content":["Place oil in mixing bowl and heat <nobr>4 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add pine nuts and heat <nobr>7 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Strain mixture through a sieve, reserving oil. Transfer pine nuts to a bowl and set aside.","Place mince, reserved oil, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then cook <nobr>10 min\/100°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer to a large bowl.","Place large bowl on mixing bowl lid then weigh in raisins, prunes, breadcrumbs, eggs and reserved pine nuts. Remove bowl and mix well with spatula. Clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Chicken","content":["Place chicken breast-side down on a chopping board and, using a boning knife or butchery scissors, cut either side of back bone. Cut down the length either side until the bone can be removed. Sprinkle interior with salt and pepper.","Place stuffing inside chicken then sew up tightly using butcher's string and a needle. Place in Varoma dish, cover and reserve. Roll any leftover stuffing into balls."]},{"title":"Sauce","content":["Place onions in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>2 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add oil and butter then cook <nobr>15 min\/Varoma\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add port, wine, water and salt. Place covered Varoma into position and steam <nobr>60 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Towards end of steaming time, preheat oven to 200°C and grease a large roasting dish.","Transfer chicken and sauce to prepared roasting dish, add stuffing balls, then roast for 25-30 minutes (200°C), until cooked thoroughly turning over halfway through. Carve chicken and serve with sauce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Stuffing","content":["70 g extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for greasing","100 g pine nuts","300 g mince (pork or chicken)","¼ - ½ tsp ground cinnamon, to taste","¼ - ½ tsp ground nutmeg, to taste","½ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","100 g raisins","100 g prunes","2 - 3 Tbsp breadcrumbs","2 medium eggs"]},{"title":"Chicken","content":["1 chicken, approx. 2 kg","1 pinch fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper"]},{"title":"Sauce","content":["300 g onions, quartered","30 g extra virgin olive oil","70 g butter, diced","180 g port","180 g dry white wine","200 g water","1 - 2 tsp fine sea salt, to taste"]}],"id":"r133209","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-z1mgzXOr-xk\/XZQu_UDbpjI\/AAAAAAAAcZY\/kwmzsmKlqsMt940pxYihsXo86YEJyfstQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_AN4X9my3OcBYsg_u.png","title":"Stuffed Christmas Chicken (Mexico)","publishedAt":"2016-12-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.8 g","fat":"26.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"16.9 g","calories":"1439 kJ \/ 344 kcal"},"usefulItems":"medium mesh sieve, large bowl, scissors, chopping block , butcher's string, roasting dish, oven","basicInfo":["medium","1h 50m","2h 10m","10 portions"]}